  "title": "Chef de Partie",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>Responsible for a specific section or station in the kitchen, overseeing the preparation of  dishes and ensuring quality and consistency.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage and oversee a specific section of the kitchen to ensure that all dishes from  the assigned station are prepared according to the restaurant's standards.  </li>\n  <li>Execute intricate and detailed cooking techniques required for fine-dining cuisine.  </li>\n  <li>Maintain high standards of food quality, taste, and presentation.  Work closely with other members of the kitchen team to coordinate the timing of  dishes.  </li>\n  <li>Assist in managing inventory for the assigned station and report to sous chef or head  chef regarding ingredient needs and shortages.  </li>\n  <li>Adhere to health and safety regulations and maintain a clean and organised station. </li>\n  <li>Carry out any ad-hoc duties as assigned.  </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements </strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Best with working experiences in a professional kitchen, with a focus on fine dining.  </li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills with good knowledge of food safety and sanitation  standards. </li>\n  <li>Team player with passion for delivering high-quality dining experiences.  Adapt to fast-paced environments.</li>\n</ul>",
